<h1>About Subnet Suite</h1>

<p><strong>Subnet Suite</strong> is a free and open subnetting toolkit designed for networking students, professionals, and anyone learning IP addressing. Whether you're preparing for your CCNA or just need a quick reference, this tool simplifies everything from VLSM calculations to visualizing your network.</p>

<h2>What’s Included</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>VLSM Calculator</strong> – Plan and split networks by required host counts</li>
    <li><strong>IPv6 Calculator</strong> – Convert, expand, and subnet IPv6 addresses</li>
    <li><strong>Supernetting Tool</strong> – Aggregate CIDR blocks into summaries</li>
    <li><strong>Interactive Visualizer</strong> – Drag-and-drop devices and auto-assign IPs to simulate topologies</li>
    <li><strong>Binary Calculations</strong> – Convert binary, hex, and decimal numbers as well as do some binary additions and subtr</li>
</ul>

<h2>Who Built This?</h2>
<p>This project was built by <strong>Connor Horning</strong>, a graduating Computer and Network Systems Administration student. It was created as both a personal learning tool and a helpful resource for fellow students.</p>

<h2>Tech Stack</h2>
<ul>
    <li>ASP.NET Core with Razor Pages</li>
    <li>HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript</li>
    <li>Custom JS logic for VLSM + Visualizer</li>
</ul>

